reviewText: Pretty animation. The teenage riders at a riding academy learn horse care and team work. The horses, dog and pig learn things too, like overcoming fear. I watched this with my daughter and even I enjoy it. The horses each have unique coloring and matching equipment and I like the story lines.
summary: Really liked, bought 2nd one as a gift!

reviewText: I don't like my kids watching commercials so it drove me crazy waiting for Horseland to come on. Saturday morning cartoons are more commercials than content. I ordered this DVD after only watching a couple episodes so I wasn't completely sure it was a great show. I am so glad I did! It has great social messages and my girls love it! The episodes are only 20 minutes long so it is great to let them watch just one while I am getting a meal ready.This is a wonderful show for girls and each show has a great moral. It is also a really good value with 39 episodes!
Title: N/A

reviewText: I literally had to turn the tv off to get my kids to stop watching this.  It's not always a "feel good" type show.  There are clicks, the "relatables" and "the rich and snooty" among the humans and horses alike.  But they are real type problems that are often found in life, and I like how they are handled so far.  One of the morals that was taught was "Don't judge a person by their limo."  It was cute, and well done.

reviewText: My daughter watches these all the time. she is obsessed with horses and plans to have her own Horse Ranch when she gets older.....she plans to name it Horseland and have it set up just how it is in the DVD's. The series is all about teaching manners and values along with knowledge about horses. The voices of the girls are very annoying to me but not to her. yes some of the characters behave badly, etc.....but there are always consequences and a lesson to be be learned in the end. For this price...it's a steal!
